  "verdict": "The three s_N probes are one frequency-resolved admittance A(omega,N)=s_N0/(1+i omega/lambda). The same N_c fold that diverges s_N0 collapses the corner lambda->0, so toward flotation every periodic probe is driven into rolloff (gain ~ s_N0*lambda/omega -> 0) while the quasi-static limit diverges \u2014 the probes coincide only well-grounded, and the rolloff sweeps DOWN through the forcing band (M2->MSf->decadal->secular), an ordered ungrounding precursor. Admittance at corner-straddling frequencies inverts s_N0 and tau_h=1/lambda SEPARATELY (s_N0 to 12%, N to 6% at 5% noise) \u2014 a new measurement disentangling sliding sensitivity from basal relaxation time, with phase lag rising to 90 deg at N_c. Calibration-free in omega/lambda; the spectroscopy measures the absolute scale the repo carries as a normalization."
